clinical_study.brief_title: Safety and Efficacy of Escalating Doses of LEO 43204 Applied Once Daily for Two Consecutive Days on Approximately 250 cm2 on Trunk and Extremities in Subjects With Actinic Keratosis
clinical_study.official_title: Safety and Efficacy of Escalating Doses of LEO 43204 Applied Once Daily for Two Consecutive Days on Approximately 250 cm2 on Trunk and Extremities in Subjects With Actinic Keratosis

brief_summary.textblock:
Part 1: To identify Maximum Tolerated Dose (MTD) levels of LEO 43204 after once daily treatment for two consecutive days
Part 2: To evaluate the efficacy of LEO 43204 in two doses after once daily treatment for two consecutive days compared to vehicle

study_design_info.masking: Quadruple (Participant, Care Provider, Investigator, Outcomes Assessor)

primary_outcome.measure: Part 1: Participants Experiencing Dose Limiting Toxicity (DLT) Based on Local Skin Responses (LSRs)
primary_outcome.time_frame: From Day 1 up to and including Day 8
primary_outcome.description: The number participants experiencing a DLT was used to identify the maximum tolerated dose(MTD) levels of LEO 43204 after once daily treatment for 2 consecutive days.The MTD was defined as the highest dose level at which less than 4 out of 12 participants experienced a DLT. A DLT was defined as one or more of the following three LSRs: Crusting Grade 4 Erosion/Ulceration Grade 4 Vesiculation/Pustulation Grade 4 or two or more of the following five LSRs: Crusting Grade 3 Swelling Grade 4 Erosion/Ulceration Grade 3 Vesiculation/Pustulation Grade 3 or other clinically relevant signs or symptoms observed, which the Investigator judged to be counted as a DLT. The LSRs consists of the following 6 categories: Erythema, flaking/scaling, crusting, swelling, vesiculation/pustulation, erosion/ulceration. Each individual LSR category was given a numeric grade of severity from 0-4. Grade 0 being no presence and Grade 4 being the highest grade of severity.

primary_outcome.measure: Part 2: Percent Reduction From Baseline in Actinic Keratosis (AK) Count
primary_outcome.description: Percent reduction from baseline in clinically visible actinic keratosis lesions (AKs) identified in the treatment area.

secondary_outcome.measure: Part 2: Participants With Complete Clearance of AKs (Last Observation Carried Forward [LOCF])
secondary_outcome.description: Complete clearance was defined as a 100% reduction from baseline in AK count.

secondary_outcome.measure: Part 2: Participants With Partial Clearance of AKs (LOCF)
secondary_outcome.description: Partial clearance was defined as at least 75% reduction from baseline in AK count.

Placebo once daily for two days

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Part 1: Subjects with 5 to 20 clinically typical, visible and discrete AKs on the arm
- Part 2: Subjects with 5 to 20 clinically typical, visible and discrete AKs on the extremities or trunk
Exclusion Criteria:
- Location of the treatment area
- within 5 cm of an incompletely healed wound
- within 5 cm of a suspected basal cell carcinoma (BCC) or squamous cell carcinoma (SCC)
- Prior treatment with ingenol mebutate gel on the treatment area
- Lesions in the treatment areas that have:
- atypical clinical appearance (e.g., hypertrophic, hyperkeratotic or cutaneous horns) and/or
- recalcitrant disease (e.g., did not respond to cryotherapy on two previous occasions)
